0 0 0 rg
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 742.00 Tm (Workshop Presenter Notes) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 724.00 Tm (School Lunch Modernization Grants Demo) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 700.00 Tm (Module 1: Setup) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 683.00 Tm (- The workshop starts with a narrow setup goal: everyone knows that Codex, Claude) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 671.00 Tm (  Code, and Python are available before the research workflow begins.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 656.00 Tm (- This opening is not really about the command line. It is about making the tools feel) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 644.00 Tm (  usable and making sure the app can run a small check when the project later needs) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 632.00 Tm (  scripts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 617.00 Tm (- The tiny Python check is the first low-stakes interaction with Codex. It gives the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 605.00 Tm (  room a concrete example of the agent running something, reading the result, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 593.00 Tm (  explaining what happened.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 578.00 Tm (- The project folder has not been created yet because folder setup is part of the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 566.00 Tm (  research workflow itself. The session starts from a realistic blank workspace, not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 554.00 Tm (  from a pre-arranged project.) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 539.00 Tm (Transition: Now that the tools are ready, we can move from setup into a real) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 526.00 Tm (research assignment.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 503.00 Tm (Module 2: PI Email To Project Memory) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 486.00 Tm (- This module turns a loose PI email into a real research project. The important shift) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 474.00 Tm (  is from a message in an inbox to a workspace with source materials, folders, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 462.00 Tm (  shared memory.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 447.00 Tm (- My_RA_Tasks is just the outer workspace. The actual research project lives inside) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 435.00 Tm (  it, which keeps the workshop folder simple while still showing how a project root) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 423.00 Tm (  gets created.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 408.00 Tm (- The PI email and raw ZIP are the source materials. The rest of the workshop feels) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 396.00 Tm (  traceable back to those original inputs, not like a disconnected coding exercise.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 381.00 Tm (- The dedicated project folder creates the boundary for the work. Once that folder is) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 369.00 Tm (  the active project root, paths like docs/ and data/original/ have a stable meaning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 354.00 Tm (- The email goes into docs/ and the unchanged ZIP goes into data/original/. That) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 342.00 Tm (  separation makes the difference between source evidence and generated work visible) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 330.00 Tm (  from the beginning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 315.00 Tm (- The handoff summary translates the PI's request into the research objective,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 303.00 Tm (  expected deliverables, open questions, and judgment calls that the project will) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 291.00 Tm (  carry forward.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 276.00 Tm (- The project memory files give future agent turns stable context. They say what the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 264.00 Tm (  project is, what gets preserved, and where the work stays conservative.) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 249.00 Tm (Transition: We now have the project set up and the PI request anchored. Next we) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 236.00 Tm (inspect the raw data before making any claims.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 213.00 Tm (Module 3: Raw Data And Role Rubric) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 196.00 Tm (- This module is about looking before acting. The panel is not being built yet; the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 184.00 Tm (  goal is to make the raw evidence understandable.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 169.00 Tm (- The raw ZIP contains several files that need to be inventoried before they become) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 157.00 Tm (  useful. Row counts, file units, and likely relationships matter because they shape) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 145.00 Tm (  every later merge.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 130.00 Tm (- The key research issue is matching. School identifiers, school names, district) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 118.00 Tm (  aliases, and crosswalk support all determine whether the final panel is trustworthy.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 103.00 Tm (- The cafeteria partner roles are where judgment enters the project. Some records) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 91.00 Tm (  clearly look like school meal-program leadership, while others look like vendors,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 79.00 Tm (  offices, advisors, or vague partners.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 28.00 Tm (Page 1 of 3) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
