BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 742.00 Tm (Module 6: Prepare The PI Handoff) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 725.00 Tm (- This module turns the data product back into research communication. The work is not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 713.00 Tm (  finished just because the panel exists.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 698.00 Tm (- The panel review memo explains what was built, what variables exist, how they were) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 686.00 Tm (  constructed, and which caveats still matter.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 671.00 Tm (- The PI update is concise, practical, and honest about uncertainty. It sounds like a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 659.00 Tm (  research handoff, not like a claim that every data issue has been solved.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 644.00 Tm (- This module shows that a good deliverable is more than a file. It is a file plus a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 632.00 Tm (  readable account of the judgment calls behind it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 617.00 Tm (- By the end of the handoff, the PI knows what is ready, what needs review, and what) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 605.00 Tm (  next analysis step is reasonable.) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 590.00 Tm (Transition: The original assignment is complete, and the same workflow can handle) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 577.00 Tm (a follow-up question when time allows.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 554.00 Tm (Module 7: Causal Spec Lab) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 537.00 Tm (- This module is the realistic follow-up: the PI asks a new question and introduces a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 525.00 Tm (  new data source after the baseline panel exists.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 510.00 Tm (- The same discipline carries forward. The follow-up request becomes source context,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 498.00 Tm (  the survey extract becomes a new raw input, and the merge has to preserve the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 486.00 Tm (  baseline panel universe.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 471.00 Tm (- The survey extract needs the same kind of inspection as the earlier raw data. Unit) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 459.00 Tm (  of observation, school-year keys, coverage, missingness, and merge readiness all) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 447.00 Tm (  matter before analysis.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 432.00 Tm (- The econometric plan is where Codex acts as a design partner. It can lay out) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 420.00 Tm (  candidate specifications, name assumptions, and explain which comparisons are) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 408.00 Tm (  descriptive, exploratory, or closer to causal.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 393.00 Tm (- The 2022 scoring change is suggestive, but it is not automatically a clean causal) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 381.00 Tm (  design. A statewide post indicator by itself is not enough for strong causal claims.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 366.00 Tm (- The spec-lab outputs are useful for patterns, estimates, plots, and careful checks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 354.00 Tm (  The final PI-facing brief separates what the analysis suggests from what remains) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 342.00 Tm (  uncertain.) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 327.00 Tm (Transition: This shows how an organized project can absorb new data and new) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 314.00 Tm (questions without losing the audit trail.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 291.00 Tm (Module 8: Publication-Style Visualizations) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 274.00 Tm (- This module shows that visual work can also be part of an agentic research workflow,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 262.00 Tm (  not just something that happens after the analysis is over.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 247.00 Tm (- The goal is not a final journal figure in one try. The goal is a serious first draft) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 235.00 Tm (  that makes visual choices explicit enough to inspect and discuss.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 220.00 Tm (- The visualization brief gives the plots a target before code is written. The four) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 208.00 Tm (  visuals cover grant timing, meal outcomes, survey outcomes, and causal-estimate) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 196.00 Tm (  caveats.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 181.00 Tm (- The plotting script turns the expanded panel and spec-lab outputs into SVG drafts) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 169.00 Tm (  after Codex installs the required visualization packages. Because the plots come) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 157.00 Tm (  from code, visual changes remain traceable if the team decides to revise later.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 142.00 Tm (- The teaching moment is visual review. Titles, labels, legends, annotations, spacing,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 130.00 Tm (  source notes, and clipping are all concrete parts of the research output.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 115.00 Tm (- The review boundary is important: visual elements can change later, while the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 103.00 Tm (  analysis and causal claims stay the same even when the plot looks polished.) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 88.00 Tm (Transition: This shows that visual work can also be prompted and inspected like) Tj ET
BT /F2 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 66.00 75.00 Tm (any other research output.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 28.00 Tm (Page 3 of 3) Tj ET
